1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
React is built on components.
Let's learn what they are.

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:08,000
A component is a reusable piece of
the user interface.

3
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:11,000
It can be as small as a button,
or as large as an entire page.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:15,000
In React, components are just
JavaScript functions that return markup.

5
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:20,000
Here's a button component.
It's a function called MyButton.

6
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:25,000
To use your component, reference it
like any other JSX element.

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:29,000
Make sure to capitalize the first letter.
That tells React it's a component.

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:33,000
You can use the same component
multiple times.

9
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:37,000
Nest components inside other components
to build complex user interfaces.

10
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:42,000
Components are the building blocks
of every React app.

11
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:46,000
Start with functions, and you
can build anything.

12
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:50,000
Next episode: learn about Props
to pass data to your components.
